sentence.text: LncRNA pancEts-1 promoted the growth, invasion, and metastasis of neuroblastoma cells in vitro and in vivo Mechanistically, pancEts-1 bound to regulation of low-density lipoprotein particle clearance to facilitate its physical interaction with β-catenin, whereas hnRNPK stabilized the β-catenin by inhibiting proteasome-mediated degradation, resulting in transcriptional alteration of target genes associated with neuroblastoma progression.
